column5: Last week the walleye moved out to the main lake, humps were loaded, especially ones that topped out between 15’’ to 20’ feet deep, although one reef that topped out at 8’ held a few decent slot fish.
Sunday morning coffee while watching Simon pound Walleye. I need to go fishing....  😆

Nah, purely scouting mission for the folks I guided today, they got 60 between them with 2x26”, 1x24”, 2 x 23” and numerous  in the 18” to 21” range and enough eaters to feed a small village. Job Done me thinks.
